# Aerial Fleet Monitor — root build-context ignore
#
# Applies to docker builds whose context is the repo root. The pipelines
# image (Dagster user-code / webserver / daemon) builds from root context
# so its Dockerfile can COPY both `pipelines/` and the sibling
# `foundry/sync/` package (the foundry sync assets import afm_foundry_sync).
#
# The `api` service builds from `./api` and is unaffected by this file.
#
# Two jobs:
#   1. Security — `_private/` and every `.env*` (except `.env.example`)
#      must NEVER enter the build context, so the Foundry bearer token
#      cannot be baked into an image layer. Creds are injected at runtime
#      via compose `env_file`, never copied.
#   2. Size — keep the root context lean (no .git, venvs, parquet lake,
#      Dagster local state, or unrelated top-level trees).

# --- Secrets / private tree (security-critical) ---
_private/
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# --- VCS ---
.git/
.gitignore
.github/

# --- Virtual envs (any package) ---
**/.venv/
**/venv/
**/env/

# --- Python build artifacts / caches ---
**/__pycache__/
**/*.py[cod]
**/*.egg-info/
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.mypy_cache/
**/.ruff_cache/
**/.coverage
**/htmlcov/

# --- Dagster local state — belongs in the DAGSTER_HOME volume, not the image ---
**/dagster_home/
**/.dagster/

# --- Tests are not shipped in the runtime image ---
**/tests/

# --- Top-level trees not needed by the pipelines image ---
api/
salesforce/
infra/
runbooks/
scripts/
docs/

# --- Docs / editor / OS noise ---
**/*.md
.DS_Store
*.swp
.idea/
.vscode/
